#31511
A cold and distant shore.~
You stand atop a rolling dune, the last marches of deep forest at your
back.  Before you lies the Dragon Sea, cold and grey under the storm.
Sheets of icy rain drift across the waves and away to the north a
lighthouse flashes its warning beacon across the sea.
 
The beach is deserted, but far far away you sense rather than hear the
sound of bells, chiming a pattern above the crash of the storm.  It is the
Rainsong, the sea elves' keen lament.  You listen enchanted, until at last
the pattern fades and is lost in the wailing of the gulls.
~
